OHL, Globalvia to Bid for Canada 407 East Contract, Cinco Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-03-12T11:16:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-12/ohl-globalvia-to-bid-for-canada-407-east-contract-cinco-says.html
  Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL)  and Fomento
de Construcciones & Contratas SA’s Globalvia infrastructure unit
have teamed up to bid for a contract to extend and manage part
of the 407 highway in Canada,  Cinco Dias  said.  The contract, to finance, build and manage the 22 kilometer
highway extension to be called the 407 East will require
investment of 2 billion Canadian dollars ($2.05 billion), the
newspaper said.  OHL will bid with Globalvia and Canadian pension fund
Borealis, the newspaper said. Grupo  Ferrovial SA (FER) , Intoll Group
and SNC-Lavalin Group will also make a joint bid for the
contract as will a group formed by Macquarie Bank Ltd.,  Germany ’s Bilfinger Berger SE and Fengate Capital, the newspaper
added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ross Larsen at   rlarsen2@bloomberg.net  